Load data

setwd("~/Shrubs-Seedlings/code/FireFootprints_analysis/")
load(file="../../compiled_data/fire_footprints/master_seedlings_vert.Rdata")

Filter to just PIPO

df %>% 
  filter(Species == "PIPO") %>% 
  group_by(Fire) %>% 
  summarize(n()) %>% 
  arrange(`n()`)

df <- df %>% 
  filter(Species == "PIPO")

Change species and site class to factors

df <- df %>% 
  mutate(Species = as.factor(Species)) %>% 
  mutate(Sdlg = as.factor(Sdlg), siteclass= as.factor(siteclass)) 
df <- droplevels(df)

Convert shrub area to sqrt

df <- df %>% 
  mutate(sqrt_shrubarea3 = sqrt(shrubarea3))

Count the seedlings

Normalize the numeric ones

normalize <- function(x) {
    return ((x - mean(x)) / sd(x))
  }
xdf <- xdf %>% mutate_if(is.numeric, normalize)

  mutate(log_shrubarea3 = log(shrubarea3+1)) %>%

Look at individual effects

Note: the plots look exactly the same but with different axes if you dont normalize the numeric predictors. So for including plots to visualize in the paper, I just use non-normalized data

eff_years <- predictorEffect("Years", LM)
plot(eff_years)

eff_shrubarea <- predictorEffect("sqrt_shrubarea3", LM)
